dfischer.utils

Class ContentTokenExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.ContentTokenExtractor

  • public class ContentTokenExtractor
extends java.lang.Object
    Extracts one ore more text tokens (variables) form a response content by first searching a text fragment and the extracting a relative token number.
    Since:
    V5.2-P
    See Also:
    ProxySnifferVarExtractorContentTokenPattern

      • extractTokens

        public int extractTokens()
        Extracts all tokens (variables) from the content. The result token of each token extractor item can be acquired thereafter by calling the method ContentTokenExtractorItem.getResultToken().
        Returns:
        the number of successful processed token extractor items.
        See Also:
        ContentTokenExtractorItem.getResultToken()
